obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (34173)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34173&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Human`
  line `Immunodeficiency Virus and Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome (Prevention and Control) Act,`
  line 2017.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 10th September, 2018 vide Notification No. S.O. 4715(E) dated 10th September 2018, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34174)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34174&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "AIDS" means Acquired Immune Deficiency Syndrome, a condition characterised by a`
  line `combination of signs and symptoms, caused by Human Immunodeficiency Virus, which attacks and`
  line `weakens the body's immune system making the HIV-positive person susceptible to life threatening`
  line `conditions or other conditions, as may be specified from time to time;`
  line
  line `(b) "capacity to consent" means ability of an individual, determined on an objective basis, to`
  line `understand and appreciate the nature and consequences of a proposed action and to make an informed`
  line `decision concerning such action;`
  line
  line `(c) "child affected by HIV" means a person below the age of eighteen years, who is HIV-positive`
  line `or whose parent or guardian (with whom such child normally resides) is HIV-positive or has lost a`
  line `parent or guardian (with whom such child resided) due to AIDS or lives in a household fostering`
  line `children orphaned by AIDS;`
  line
  line `(d) "discrimination" means any act or omission which directly or indirectly, expressly or by`
  line `effect, immediately or over a period of time,---`
  line
  line `(i) imposes any burden, obligation, liability, disability or disadvantage on any person or`
  line `category of persons, based on one or more HIV-related grounds; or`
  line
  line `(ii) denies or withholds any benefit, opportunity or advantage from any person or category of`
  line `persons, based on one or more HIV-related grounds,`
  line
  line `and the expression "discriminate" to be construed accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.---For the purposes of this clause, HIV-related grounds include---`
  line
  line `(i) being an HIV-positive person;`
  line
  line `(ii) ordinarily living, residing or cohabiting with a person who is HIV-positive person;`
  line
  line `(iii) ordinarily lived, resided or cohabited with a person who was HIV-positive.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.---For the removal of doubts, it is hereby clarified that adoption of medically`
  line `advised safeguards and precautions to minimise the risk of infection shall not amount to`
  line discrimination;
  line
  line `(e) "domestic relationship" means a relationship as defined under clause (f) of section 2 of the`
  line `Protection of Women from Domestic Violence Act, 2005 (43 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(f) "establishment" means a body corporate or co-operative society or any organisation or institution`
  line `or two or more persons jointly carrying out a systematic activity for a period of twelve months or more at`
  line `one or more places for consideration or otherwise, for the production, supply or distribution of goods or`
  line services;
  line
  line `(g) "guidelines" means any statement or any other document issued by the Central Government`
  line `indicating policy or procedure or course of action relating to HIV and AIDS to be followed by the Central`
  line `Government, State Governments, governmental and non-governmental organisations and establishments`
  line `and individuals dealing with prevention, control and treatment of HIV or AIDS;`
  line
  line `(h) "healthcare provider" means any individual whose vocation or profession is directly or`
  line `indirectly related to the maintenance of the health of another individual and includes any physician,`
  line `nurse, paramedic, psychologist, counsellor or other individual providing medical, nursing,`
  line `psychological or other healthcare services including HIV prevention and treatment services;`
  line
  line `(i) "HIV" means Human Immunodeficiency Virus;`
  line
  line `(j) "HIV-affected person" means an individual who is HIV-positive or whose partner (with whom`
  line `such individual normally resides) is HIV-positive or has lost a partner (with whom such individual`
  line `resided) due to AIDS;`
  line
  line `(k) "HIV-positive person" means a person whose HIV test has been confirmed positive;`
  line
  line `(l) "HIV-related information" means any information relating to the HIV status of a person and`
  line includes---
  line
  line `(i) information relating to the undertaking performing the HIV test or result of an HIV test;`
  line
  line `(ii) information relating to the care, support or treatment of that person;`
  line
  line `(iii) information which may identify that person; and`
  line
  line `(iv) any other information concerning that person, which is collected, received, accessed or`
  line `recorded in connection with an HIV test, HIV treatment or HIV-related research or the HIV status`
  line `of that person;`
  line
  line `(m) "HIV test" means a test to determine the presence of an antibody or antigen of HIV;`
  line
  line `(n) "informed consent" means consent given by any individual or his representative specific to a`
  line `proposed intervention without any coercion, undue influence, fraud, mistake or misrepresentation and such`
  line `consent obtained after informing such individual or his representative, as the case may be, such`
  line `information, as specified in the guidelines, relating to risks and benefits of, and alternatives to, the`
  line `proposed intervention in such language and in such manner as understood by that individual or his`
  line `representative, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(o) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(p) "partner" means a spouse, de facto spouse or a person with whom another person has`
  line `relationship in the nature of marriage;`
  line
  line `(q) "person" includes an individual, a Hindu Undivided Family, a company, a firm, an association`
  line `of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not, in India or outside India, any`
  line `corporation established by or under any Central or State Act or any company including a Government`
  line `company incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), any Limited Liability Partnership`
  line `under the Limited Liability Partnership Act, 2008 (6 of 2009), any body corporate incorporated by or`
  line `under the laws of a country outside India, a co-operative society registered under any law relating to`
  line `co-operative societies, a local authority, and every other artificial juridical person;`
  line
  line `(r) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(s) "protected person" means a person who is---`
  line
  line `(i) HIV-Positive; or`
  line
  line `(ii) ordinarily living, residing or cohabiting with a person who is HIV-positive person; or`
  line
  line `(iii) ordinarily lived, resided or cohabited with a person who was HIV-positive;`
  line
  line `(t) "reasonable accommodation" means minor adjustments to a job or work that enables an`
  line `HIV-positive person who is otherwise qualified to enjoy equal benefits or to perform the essential`
  line `functions of the job or work, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(u) "relative", with reference to the protected person, means---`
  line
  line `(i) spouse of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(ii) parents of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(iii) brother or sister of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(iv) brother or sister of the spouse of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(v) brother or sister of either of the parents of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(vi) in the absence of any of the relatives mentioned at sub-clauses (i) to (v), any lineal`
  line `ascendant or descendant of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(vii) in the absence of any of the relatives mentioned at sub-clauses (i) to (vi), any lineal`
  line `ascendant or descendant of the spouse of the protected person;`
  line
  line `(v) "significant-risk" means---`
  line
  line `(a) the presence of significant-risk body substances;`
  line
  line `(b) a circumstance which constitutes significant-risk for transmitting or contracting HIV`
  line `infection; or`
  line
  line `(c) the presence of an infectious source and an uninfected person.`
  line
  line `Explanation.---For the purpose of this clause,---`
  line
  line `(i) "significant-risk body substances" are blood, blood products, semen, vaginal secretions,`
  line `breast milk, tissue and the body fluids, namely, cerebrospinal, amniotic, peritoneal, synovial,`
  line `pericardial and pleural;`
  line
  line `(ii) "circumstances which constitute significant-risk for transmitting or contracting HIV`
  line `infection" are---`
  line
  line `(A) sexual intercourse including vaginal, anal or oral sexual intercourse which exposes an`
  line `uninfected person to blood, blood products, semen or vaginal secretions of an HIV-positive`
  line person;
  line
  line `(B) sharing of needles and other paraphernalia used for preparing and injecting drugs`
  line `between HIV-positive persons and uninfected persons;`
  line
  line `(C) the gestation, giving birth or breast feeding of an infant when the mother is an`
  line `HIV-positive person;`
  line
  line `(D) transfusion of blood, blood products, and transplantation of organs or other tissues`
  line `from an HIV-positive person to an uninfected person, provided such blood, blood products,`
  line `organs or other tissues have not been tested conclusively for the antibody or antigen of HIV`
  line `and have not been rendered non-infective by heat or chemical treatment; and`
  line
  line `(E) other circumstances during which a significant-risk body substance, other than breast`
  line `milk, of an HIV-positive person contacts or may contact mucous membranes including eyes,`
  line `nose or mouth, non-intact skin including open wounds, skin with a dermatitis condition or`
  line `abraded areas or the vascular system of an uninfected person, and including such`
  line `circumstances not limited to needle-stick or puncture wound injuries and direct saturation or`
  line `permeation of these body surfaces by the significant-risk body substances:`
  line
  line `Provided that "significant-risk" shall not include---`
  line
  line `(i) exposure to urine, faeces, sputum, nasal secretions, saliva, sweat, tears or vomit`
  line `that does not contain blood that is visible to the naked eye;`
  line
  line `(ii) human bites where there is no direct blood to blood, or no blood to mucous`
  line `membrane contact;`
  line
  line `(iii) exposure of intact skin to blood or any other blood substance; and`
  line
  line `(iv) occupational centres where individuals use scientifically accepted Universal`
  line `Precautions, prohibitive techniques and preventive practices in circumstances which`
  line `would otherwise pose a significant-risk and such techniques are not breached and remain`
  line intact;
  line
  line `(w) "State AIDS Control Society" means the nodal agency of the State Government responsible`
  line `for implementing programmes in the field of HIV and AIDS;`
  line
  line `(x) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator of that Union`
  line `territory appointed by the President under article 239 of the Constitution; and`
  line
  line `(y) "Universal Precautions" means control measures that prevent exposure to or reduce, the risk`
  line `of transmission of pathogenic agents (including HIV) and includes education, training, personal`
  line `protective equipment such as gloves, gowns and masks, hand washing, and employing safe work`
  line practices.
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34175)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Prohibition of discrimination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34175&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `No person shall discriminate against the protected person on any`
  line `ground including any of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the denial of, or termination from, employment or occupation, unless, in the case of`
  line `termination, the person, who is otherwise qualified, is furnished with—`
  line
  line `(i) a copy of the written assessment of a qualified and independent healthcare provider`
  line `competent to do so that such protected person poses a significant risk of transmission of HIV to`
  line `other person in the workplace, or is unfit to perform the duties of the job; and`
  line
  line `(ii) a copy of a written statement by the employer stating the nature and extent of`
  line `administrative or financial hardship for not providing him reasonable accommodation;`
  line
  line `(b) the unfair treatment in, or in relation to, employment or occupation;`
  line
  line `(c) the denial or discontinuation of, or, unfair treatment in, healthcare services;`
  line
  line `(d) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment in, educational, establishments and`
  line `services thereof;`
  line
  line `(e) the denial or discontinuation of, or unfair treatment with regard to, access to, or provision or`
  line `enjoyment or use of any goods, accommodation, service, facility, benefit, privilege or opportunity`
  line `dedicated to the use of the general public or customarily available to the public, whether or not for a`
  line `fee, including shops, public restaurants, hotels and places of public entertainment or the use of wells,`
  line `tanks, bathing ghats, roads, burial grounds or funeral ceremonies and places of public resort;`
  line
  line `(f) the denial, or, discontinuation of, or unfair treatment with regard to, the right of movement;`
  line
  line `(g) the denial or discontinuation of, or, unfair treatment with regard to, the right to reside,`
  line `purchase, rent, or otherwise occupy, any property;`
  line
  line `(h) the denial or discontinuation of, or, unfair treatment in, the opportunity to stand for, or, hold`
  line `public or private office;`
  line
  line `(i) the denial of access to, removal from, or unfair treatment in, Government or private`
  line `establishment in whose care or custody a person may be;`
  line
  line `(j) the denial of, or unfair treatment in, the provision of insurance unless supported by actuarial`
  line studies;
  line
  line `(k) the isolation or segregation of a protected person;`
  line
  line `(l) HIV testing as a pre-requisite for obtaining employment, or accessing healthcare services or`
  line `education or, for the continuation of the same or, for accessing or using any other service or facility:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case of failure to furnish the written assessment under sub-clause (i) of`
  line `clause (a), it shall be presumed that there is no significant-risk and that the person is fit to perform the`
  line `duties of the job, as the case may be, and in case of the failure to furnish the written statement under`
  line `sub-clause (ii) of that clause, it shall be presumed that there is no such undue administrative or`
  line `financial hardship.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (34176)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34176&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No person shall, by words, either spoken or written, publish,`
  line `propagate, advocate or communicate by signs or by visible representation or otherwise the feelings of`
  line `hatred against any protected persons or group of protected person in general or specifically or`
  line `disseminate, broadcast or display any information, advertisement or notice, which may reasonably be`
  line `construed to demonstrate an intention to propagate hatred or which is likely to expose protected persons`
  line `to hatred, discrimination or physical violence.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (34177)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Informed consent for undertaking HIV test or treatment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34177&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this`
  line Act,—
  line
  line `(a) no HIV test shall be undertaken or performed upon any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) no protected person shall be subject to medical treatment, medical interventions or research,`
  line
  line `except with the informed consent of such person or his representative and in such manner, as may be`
  line `specified in the guidelines.`
  line
  line `(2) The informed consent for HIV test shall include pre-test and post-test counselling to the person`
  line `being tested or such persons representative in the manner as may be specified in the guidelines.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (34178)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Informed consent not required for conducting HIV tests in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34178&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The informed`
  line `consent for conducting an HIV test shall not be required—`
  line
  line `(a) where a court determines, by an order that the carrying out of the HIV test of any person`
  line `either as part of a medical examination or otherwise, is necessary for the determination of issues in`
  line `the matter before it;`
  line
  line `(b) for procuring, processing, distribution or use of a human body or any part thereof including`
  line `tissues, blood, semen or other body fluids for use in medical research or therapy:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the test results are requested by a donor prior to donation, the donor shall be`
  line `referred to counselling and testing centre and such donor shall not be entitled to the results of the test`
  line `unless he has received post-test counselling from such centre;`
  line
  line `(c) for epidemiological or surveillance purposes where the HIV test is anonymous and is not for`
  line `the purpose of determining the HIV status of a person:`
  line
  line `Provided that persons who are subjects of such epidemiological or surveillance studies shall be`
  line `informed of the purposes of such studies; and`
  line
  line `(d) for screening purposes in any licensed blood bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (34179)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Guidelines for testing centres, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34179&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No HIV test shall be conducted or performed by any testing`
  line `or diagnostic centre or pathology laboratory or blood bank, unless such centre or laboratory or blood bank`
  line `follows the guidelines laid down for such test.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (34180)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Disclosure of HIV status.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34180&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force,—`
  line
  line `(i) no person shall be compelled to disclose his HIV status except by an order of the court that the`
  line `disclosure of such information is necessary in the interest of justice for the determination of issues in`
  line `the matter before it;`
  line
  line `(ii) no person shall disclose or be compelled to disclose the HIV status or any other private`
  line `information of other person imparted in confidence or in a relationship of a fiduciary nature, except`
  line `with the informed consent of that other person or a representative of such another person obtained in`
  line `the manner as specified in section 5, as the case may be, and the fact of such consent has been`
  line `recorded in writing by the person making such disclosure:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case of a relationship of a fiduciary nature, informed consent shall be recorded`
  line `in writing.`
  line
  line `(2) The informed consent for disclosure of HIV-related information under clause (ii) of`
  line `sub-section (1) is not required where the disclosure is made—`
  line
  line `(a) by a healthcare provider to another healthcare provider who is involved in the care, treatment`
  line `or counselling of such person, when such disclosure is necessary to provide care or treatment to that`
  line person;
  line
  line `(b) by an order of a court that the disclosure of such information is necessary in the interest of`
  line `justice for the determination of issues and in the matter before it;`
  line
  line `(c) in suits or legal proceedings between persons, where the disclosure of such information is`
  line `necessary in filing suits or legal proceedings or for instructing their counsel;`
  line
  line `(d) as required under the provisions of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) if it relates to statistical or other information of a person that could not reasonably be expected`
  line `to lead to the identification of that person; and`
  line
  line `(f) to the officers of the Central Government or the State Government or State AIDS Control`
  line `Society of the concerned State Government, as the case may be, for the purposes of monitoring,`
  line `evaluation or supervision.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (34181)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Disclosure of HIV-positive status to partner of HIV-positive person.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34181&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) No healthcare`
  line `provider, except a physician or a counsellor, shall disclose the HIV-positive status of a person to his or`
  line `her partner.`
  line
  line `(2) A healthcare provider, who is a physician or counsellor, may disclose the HIV-positive status of a`
  line `person under his direct care to his or her partner, if such healthcare provider—`
  line
  line `(a) reasonably believes that the partner is at the significant risk of transmission of HIV from such`
  line `person; and`
  line
  line `(b) such HIV-positive person has been counselled to inform such partner; and`
  line
  line `(c) is satisfied that the HIV-positive person will not inform such partner; and`
  line
  line `(d) has informed the HIV-positive person of the intention to disclose the HIV positive status to`
  line `such partner:`
  line
  line `Provided that disclosure under this sub-section to the partner shall be made in person after`
  line `counselling:`
  line
  line `Provided further that such healthcare provider shall have no obligation to identify or locate the`
  line `partner of an HIV-positive person:`
  line
  line `Provided also that such healthcare provider shall not inform the partner of a woman where there is a`
  line `reasonable apprehension that such information may result in violence, abandonment or actions which may`
  line `have a severe negative effect on the physical or mental health or safety of such woman, her children, her`
  line `relatives or someone who is close to her.`
  line
  line `(3) The healthcare provider under sub-section (1) shall not be liable for any criminal or civil action`
  line `for any disclosure or non-disclosure of confidential HIV-related information made to a partner under this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (34182)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Duty to prevent transmission of HIV.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34182&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Every person, who is HIV-positive and has been`
  line `counselled in accordance with the guidelines issued or is aware of the nature of HIV and its transmission,`
  line `shall take all reasonable precautions to prevent the transmission of HIV to other persons which may`
  line `include adopting strategies for the reduction of risk or informing in advance his HIV status before any`
  line `sexual contact with any person or with whom needles are shared with:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this section shall not be applicable to prevent transmission through a`
  line `sexual contact in the case of a woman, where there is a reasonable apprehension that such information`
  line `may result in violence, abandonment or actions which may have a severe negative effect on the physical`
  line `or mental health or safety of such woman, her children, her relatives or someone who is close to her.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (34183)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Confidentiality of data.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34183&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Every establishment keeping the records of HIV-related information of`
  line `protected persons shall adopt data protection measures in accordance with the guidelines to ensure that`
  line `such information is protected from disclosure.`
  line
  line `Explanation.— For the purpose of this section, data protection measures shall include procedures for`
  line `protecting information from disclosure, procedures for accessing information, provision for security`
  line `systems to protect the information stored in any form and mechanisms to ensure accountability and`
  line `liability of persons in the establishment.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (34184)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `HIV and AIDS policy for establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34184&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall notify model HIV`
  line `and AIDS policy for establishments, in such manner, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (34185)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Central Government and State Government to take measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34185&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and`
  line `every State Government, as the case may be, shall take all such measures as it deems necessary and`
  line `expedient for the prevention of spread of HIV or AIDS, in accordance with the guidelines.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (34223)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Anti-retroviral Therapy and Opportunistic Infection Management by Central Government and State Government`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34223&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The measures to be taken by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government under section 13 shall include the measures for providing, as far as possible, diagnostic`
  line `facilities relating to HIV or AIDS, Anti-retroviral Therapy and Opportunistic Infection Management to`
  line `people living with HIV or AIDS.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall issue necessary guidelines in respect of protocols for HIV and`
  line `AIDS relating to diagnostic facilities, Anti-retroviral Therapy and Opportunistic Infection Management`
  line `which shall be applicable to all persons and shall ensure their wide dissemination.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (34187)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Welfare measures by Central Government and State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34187&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government and every State Government shall take measures to facilitate better access to welfare`
  line `schemes to persons infected or affected by HIV or AIDS.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Central Government and State`
  line `Governments shall frame schemes to address the needs of all protected persons.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (34188)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Protection of property of children affected by HIV or AIDS.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34188&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government or`
  line `the State Government, as the case may be, shall take appropriate steps to protect the property of children`
  line `affected by HIV or AIDS for the protection of property of child affected by HIV or AIDS.`
  line
  line `(2) The parents or guardians of children affected by HIV and AIDS, or any person acting for`
  line `protecting their interest, or a child affected by HIV and AIDS may approach the Child Welfare`
  line `Committee for the safe keeping and deposit of documents related to the property rights of such child or to`
  line `make complaints relating to such child being dispossessed or actual dispossession or trespass into such`
  line `child's house.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this section, "Child Welfare Committee" means a Committee`
  line `set-up under section 29 of the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2000 (56 of 2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (34189)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Promotion of HIV and AIDS related information, education and communication programmes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34189&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and the State Government shall formulate HIV and AIDS`
  line `related information, education and communication programmes which are age-appropriate,`
  line `gender-sensitive, non-stigmatising and non-discriminatory.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (34190)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Women and children infected with HIV or AIDS.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34190&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall lay`
  line `down guidelines for care, support and treatment of children infected with HIV or AIDS.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (1) and notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Central Government, or the State`
  line `Government as the case may be, shall take measures to counsel and provide information regarding the`
  line `outcome of pregnancy and HIV-related treatment to the HIV infected women.`
  line
  line `(3) No HIV positive woman, who is pregnant, shall be subjected to sterilisation or abortion without`
  line `obtaining her informed consent.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (34191)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Obligation of establishments to provide safe working environment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34191&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Every establishment,`
  line `engaged in the healthcare services and every such other establishment where there is a significant risk of`
  line `occupational exposure to HIV, shall, for the purpose of ensuring safe working environment,—`
  line
  line `(i) provide, in accordance with the guidelines,—`
  line
  line `(a) Universal Precautions to all persons working in such establishment who may be`
  line `occupationally exposed to HIV; and`
  line
  line `(b) training for the use of such Universal Precautions;`
  line
  line `(c) Post Exposure Prophylaxis to all persons working in such establishment who may be`
  line `occupationally exposed to HIV or AIDS; and`
  line
  line `(ii) inform and educate all persons working in the establishment of the availability of Universal`
  line `Precautions and Post Exposure Prophylaxis.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (34192)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `General responsibility of establishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34192&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Chapter shall be`
  line `applicable to all establishments consisting of one hundred or more persons, whether as an employee or`
  line `officer or member or director or trustee or manager, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of healthcare establishments, the provisions of this sub-section shall have the`
  line `effect as if for the words "one hundred or more", the words "twenty or more" had been substituted.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person, who is in charge of an establishment, referred to in sub-section (1), for the conduct`
  line `of the activities of such establishment, shall ensure compliance of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (34193)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Grievance redressal mechanism.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34193&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Every establishment referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 20 shall designate such person, as it deems fit, as the Complaints Officer who shall dispose of`
  line `complaints of violations of the provisions of this Act in the establishment, in such manner and within`
  line `such time as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (34194)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Strategies for reduction of risk.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34194&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the`
  line `time being in force any strategy or mechanism or technique adopted or implemented for reducing the risk`
  line `of HIV transmission, or any act pursuant thereto, as carried out by persons, establishments or`
  line `organisations in the manner as may be specified in the guidelines issued by the Central Government shall`
  line `not be restricted or prohibited in any manner, and shall not amount to a criminal offence or attract civil`
  line liability.
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purpose of this section, strategies for reducing risk of HIV transmission means`
  line `promoting actions or practices that minimise a person's risk of exposure to HIV or mitigate the adverse`
  line `impacts related to HIV or AIDS including---`
  line
  line `(i) the provisions of information, education and counselling services relating to prevention of`
  line `HIV and safe practices;`
  line
  line `(ii) the provisions and use of safer sex tools, including condoms;`
  line
  line `(iii) drug substitution and drug maintenance; and`
  line
  line `(iv) provision of comprehensive injection safety requirements.`
  line
  line Illustrations
  line
  line `(a) A supplies condoms to B who is a sex worker or to C, who is a client of B. Neither A nor B`
  line `nor C can be held criminally or civilly liable for such actions or be prohibited, impeded, restricted or`
  line `prevented from implementing or using the strategy.`
  line
  line `(b) M carries on an intervention project on HIV or AIDS and sexual health information,`
  line `education and counselling for men, who have sex with men, provides safer sex information, material`
  line `and condoms to N, who has sex with other men. Neither M nor N can be held criminally or civilly`
  line `liable for such actions or be prohibited, impeded, restricted or prevented from implementing or using`
  line `the intervention.`
  line
  line `(c) X, who undertakes an intervention providing registered needle exchange programme services`
  line `to injecting drug users, supplies a clean needle to Y, an injecting drug user who exchanges the same`
  line `for a used needle. Neither X nor Y can be held criminally or civilly liable for such actions or be`
  line `prohibited, impeded, restricted or prevented from implementing or using the intervention.`
  line
  line `(d) D, who carries on an intervention programme providing Opioid Substitution Treatment`
  line `(OST), administers OST to E, an injecting drug user. Neither D nor E can be held criminally or civilly`
  line `liable for such actions or be prohibited, impeded, restricted or prevented from implementing or using`
  line `the intervention.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (34195)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Appointment of Ombudsman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34195&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every State Government shall appoint one or more`
  line Ombudsman,—
  line
  line `(a) possessing such qualification and experience as may be prescribed, or`
  line
  line `(b) designate any of its officers not below such rank, as may be prescribed, by that Government,`
  line
  line `to exercise such powers and discharge such functions, as may be conferred on Ombudsman under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) The terms and condition of the service of an Ombudsman appointed under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Ombudsman appointed under sub-section (1) shall have such jurisdiction in respect of such`
  line `area or areas as the State Government may, by notification, specify.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (34196)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers of Ombudsman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34196&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Ombudsman shall, upon a complaint made by any person,`
  line `inquire into the violations of the provisions of this Act, in relation to acts of discrimination mentioned in`
  line `section 3 and providing of healthcare services by any person, in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Ombudsman may require any person to furnish information on such points or matters, as he`
  line `considers necessary, for inquiring into the matter and any person so required shall be deemed to be legally`
  line `bound to furnish such information and failure to do so shall be punishable under sections 176 and 177 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(3) The Ombudsman shall maintain records in such manner as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (34197)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Procedure of complaint.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34197&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The complaints may be made to the Ombudsman under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 24 in such manner, as may be prescribed, by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (34198)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Orders of Ombudsman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34198&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Ombudsman shall, within a period of thirty days of the receipt of`
  line `the complaint under sub-section (1) of section 24, and after giving an opportunity of being heard to the`
  line `parties, pass such order, as he deems fit, giving reasons therefor:`
  line
  line `Provided that in cases of medical emergency of HIV positive persons, the Ombudsman shall pass`
  line `such order as soon as possible, preferably within twenty-four hours of the receipt of the complaint.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (34199)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Authorities to assist Ombudsman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34199&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `All authorities including the civil authorities functioning in`
  line `the area for which the Ombudsman has been appointed under section 23 shall assist in execution of orders`
  line `passed by the Ombudsman.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (34200)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Report to State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34200&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `The Ombudsman shall, after every six months, report to the`
  line `State Government, the number and nature of complaints received, the action taken and orders passed in`
  line `relation to such complaints and such report shall be published on the website of the Ombudsman and a`
  line `copy thereof be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (34201)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Right of residence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34201&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Every protected person shall have the right to reside in the shared`
  line `household, the right not to be excluded from the shared household or any part of it and the right to enjoy`
  line `and use the facilities of such shared household in a non-discriminatory manner.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, the expression "shared household" means a household`
  line `where a person lives or at any stage has lived in a domestic relationship either singly or along with`
  line `another person and includes such a household, whether owned or tenanted, either jointly or singly, any`
  line `such household in respect of which either person or both, jointly or singly, have any right, title, interest or`
  line `equity or a household which may belong to a joint family of which either person is a member, irrespective`
  line `of whether either person has any right, title or interest in the shared household.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (34202)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `HIV-related information, education and communication before marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34202&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Central`
  line `Government shall specify guidelines for the provision of HIV-related information, education and`
  line `communication before marriage and ensure their wide dissemination.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (34203)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Persons in care or custody of State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34203&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person who is in the care or custody of the State`
  line `shall have the right to HIV prevention, counselling, testing and treatment services in accordance with the`
  line `guidelines issued in this regard.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of this section, persons in the care or custody of the State include persons`
  line `convicted of a crime and serving a sentence, persons awaiting trial, person detained under preventive`
  line `detention laws, persons under the care or custody of the State under the Juvenile Justice (Care and`
  line `Protection of Children) Act, 2000 (56 of 2000), the Immoral Traffic (Prevention) Act, 1956 (104 of 1956)`
  line `or any other law and persons in the care or custody of State run homes and shelters.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (34204)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Recognition of guardianship of older sibling.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34204&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any law`
  line `for the time being in force, a person below the age of eighteen but not below twelve years, who has`
  line `sufficient maturity of understanding and who is managing the affairs of his family affected by HIV and`
  line `AIDS, shall be competent to act as guardian of other sibling below the age of eighteen years for the`
  line `following purposes, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) admission to educational establishments;`
  line
  line `(b) care and protection;`
  line
  line `(c) treatment;`
  line
  line `(d) operating bank accounts;`
  line
  line `(e) managing property; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other purpose that may be required to discharge his duties as a guardian.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this section, a family affected by HIV or AIDS means where both`
  line `parents and the legal guardian is incapacitated due to HIV-related illness or AIDS or the legal guardian`
  line `and parents are unable to discharge their duties in relation to such children.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (34205)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Living wills for guardianship and testamentary guardianship.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34205&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any law for the time being in force, a parent or legal guardian of a child affected by HIV and AIDS may appoint, by making a will, an adult person who is a relative or friend, or a person below the`
  line `age of eighteen years who is the managing member of the family affected by HIV and AIDS, as referred`
  line `to in section 33, to act as legal guardian immediately upon incapacity or death of such parent or legal`
  line `guardian, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this section shall divest a parent or legal guardian of their rights, and the guardianship`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) shall cease to operate upon by the parent or legal guardian regaining their`
  line capacity.
  line
  line `(3) Any parent or legal guardian of children affected by HIV and AIDS may make a will appointing a`
  line `guardian for care and protection of such children and for the property that such children would inherit or`
  line `which is bequeathed through the will made by such parent or legal guardian.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (34206)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Suppression of identity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34206&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any legal proceeding in which a protected person is a party or`
  line `such person is an applicant, the court, on an application by such person or any other person on his behalf`
  line `may pass, in the interest of justice, any or all of the following orders, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) that the proceeding or any part thereof be conducted by suppressing the identity of the`
  line `applicant by substituting the name of such person with a pseudonym in the records of the proceedings`
  line `in such manner as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `(b) that the proceeding or any part thereof may be conducted in camera;`
  line
  line `(c) restraining any person from publishing in any manner any matter leading to the disclosure of`
  line `the name or status or identity of the applicant.`
  line
  line `(2) In any legal proceeding concerning or relating to an HIV-positive person, the court shall take up`
  line `and dispose of the proceeding on priority basis.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (34207)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Maintenance applications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34207&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `In any maintenance application filed by or on behalf of a protected`
  line `person under any law for the time being in force, the court shall consider the application for interim`
  line `maintenance and, in passing any order of maintenance, shall take into account the medical expenses and`
  line `other HIV-related costs that may be incurred by the applicant.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (34208)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title Sentencing.
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34208&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `In passing any order relating to sentencing, the HIV-positive status of the persons`
  line `in respect of whom such an order is passed shall be a relevant factor to be considered by the court to`
  line `determine the custodial place where such person shall be transferred to, based on the availability of proper`
  line `healthcare services at such place.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (34209)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Penalty for contravention.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34209&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any action that may be taken under any other law`
  line `for the time being in force, whoever contravenes the provisions of section 4 shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which may extend to two years and`
  line `with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (34210)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Ombudsman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34210&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails to comply with any`
  line `order given by an Ombudsman within such time as may be specified in such order, under section 26, shall`
  line `be liable to pay a fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees and in case the failure continues, with an`
  line `additional fine which may extend to five thousand rupees for every day during which such failure`
  line continues.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (34211)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Penalty for breach of confidentiality in legal proceeding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34211&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding any action that`
  line `may be taken under any law for the time being in force, whoever discloses information regarding the HIV`
  line `status of a protected person which is obtained by him in the course of, or in relation to, any proceedings`
  line `before any court, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees unless such`
  line `disclosure is pursuant to any order or direction of a court.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (34212)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Prohibition of victimisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34212&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `No person shall subject any other person or persons to any`
  line `detriment on the ground that such person or persons have taken any of the following actions, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) made complaint under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) brought proceedings under this Act against any person;`
  line
  line `(c) furnished any information or produced any document to a person exercising or performing`
  line `any power or function under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(d) appeared as a witness in a proceeding under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (34213)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Court to try offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34213&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `No court other than the court of a Judicial Magistrate First Class shall`
  line `take cognizance of an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (34214)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Offences to be cognizable and bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34214&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), offences under this Act shall be cognizable and bailable.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (34215)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34215&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (34216)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34216&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government, the State Government, the Central Government or AIDS Control`
  line `Society of the State Government Ombudsman or any member thereof or any officer or other employee or`
  line `person acting under the direction either of the Central Government, the State Government, the Central`
  line `Government, or Ombudsman in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of this Act or any rules or guidelines made thereunder or in respect of the publication by or`
  line `under the authority of the Central Government, the State Government, the Central Government or AIDS`
  line `Control Society of the State Government Ombudsman.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (34217)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34217&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government and State Government, as the case may be,`
  line `may, by general or special order, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall, in such`
  line `circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be mentioned in the order, be exercisable also by`
  line `an officer subordinate to that Government or the local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (34218)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title Guidelines.
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34218&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, make guidelines consistent with`
  line `this Act and any rules thereunder, generally to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such guidelines may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) information relating to risk and benefits or alternatives to the proposed intervention under`
  line `clause (n) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of obtaining the informed consent under sub-section (1) and the manner of pre test`
  line `and post test counselling under sub-section (2) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) guidelines to be followed by a testing or diagnostic centre or pathology laboratory or blood`
  line `bank for HIV test under section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of taking data protection measures under section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) guidelines in respect of protocols for HIV/AIDS relating to Anti-retroviral Therapy and`
  line `Opportunistic Infections Management under sub-section (2) of section 14;`
  line
  line `(f) care, support and treatment of children infected with HIV or AIDS under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(g) guidelines for Universal Precautions and post exposure prophylaxis under section 19;`
  line
  line `(h) manner of carrying out the strategy or mechanism or technique for reduction of risk of HIV`
  line `transmission under section 22;`
  line
  line `(i) manner of implementation of a drugs substitution, drug maintenance and needle and syringe`
  line `exchange programme under section 22;`
  line
  line `(j) provision of HIV-related information, education and communication before marriage under`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(k) manner of HIV or AIDS prevention, counselling, testing and treatment of persons in custody`
  line `under section 31;`
  line
  line `(l) any other matter which ought to be specified in guidelines for the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (34219)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34219&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provision, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) manner of notifying model HIV or AIDS policy for the establishments under section 12;`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter which may be or ought to be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (34220)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Laying of rules before both Houses of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34220&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be`
  line `laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and`
  line `if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive session aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be`
  line `made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may`
  line `be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (34221)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Power of State Government to make rules and laying thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34221&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government`
  line `may, by notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) measures to provide diagnostic facilities relating to HIV or AIDS, Antiretroviral Therapy and`
  line `Opportunistic Infection Management to people living with HIV or AIDS and for the prevention of`
  line `spread of HIV or AIDS in accordance with the guidelines under section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) qualification and experience for the appointment of a person as an Ombudsman under`
  line `clause (a) or rank of officer of the State Government to be designated as Ombudsman under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(c) terms and conditions of services of Ombudsman under sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(d) manner of inquiring into complaints by the Ombudsman under sub-section (1) and`
  line `maintaining of records by him under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(e) manner of making the complaints to the Ombudsman under section 25; and`
  line
  line `(f) manner of recording pseudonym in legal proceedings under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 34.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it`
  line `is made before the Legislature of that State.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (34222)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383&sectionId=34222&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00021_201716_1517807327383
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of the period of two years`
  line `from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
